# Sports ML Lab Agent Rules

## System Configuration
- OpenCode runs on MacBook
- LLM models are hosted remotely on System76 laptop via internal LAN Ollama API
- Do not modify Ollama, OpenCode, provider, network, SSH, API or model configuration

## Research Practices
- Run lightweight tests locally
- Do not run long full training jobs locally unless asked
- Do not modify raw historical data
- Do not use future data in features
- Every feature must be explainable and pregame-safe
- Every experiment must report: log loss, Brier score, accuracy, calibration notes and leakage risk
- Never promote a model based on ROI alone

## Data Usage
- No modification of raw historical data
- All datasets are read-only for research purposes
- Features are always created from available pregame information only
- Strict adherence to causality principles in feature engineering

## Model Development
- Models are developed with reproducible ML practices
- Prioritize explainability over predictive power where feasible
- Focus on building a foundation before implementing full features